WEBVTT

00:06.621 --> 00:08.087
Did you get any sleep?

00:08.089 --> 00:11.491
Oh, a couple minutes
here and there. You?

00:11.492 --> 00:14.461
No, I kept waking up from
nightmares about Russia

00:14.462 --> 00:16.229
infiltrating the top
levels of our government.

00:16.230 --> 00:18.064
- Mm.
- More coffee?

00:18.065 --> 00:19.766
Sure.

00:19.767 --> 00:21.902
I'm already on my second pot.

00:21.903 --> 00:25.872
So have you found any reason
not to suspect the Gang of Eight?

00:25.873 --> 00:28.408
Besides the fact that they're
the most powerful members

00:28.409 --> 00:30.877
of Congress and it would be
treason for any one of them

00:30.878 --> 00:33.313
to share our secrets with Russia? Nah.

00:33.314 --> 00:36.149
I've had my team working
on it all night, too.

00:36.150 --> 00:37.250
Eggs?

00:37.251 --> 00:40.654
No. I'm feeling carby.

00:40.655 --> 00:44.524
You'll want rock-solid proof

00:44.525 --> 00:46.359
before you take it up the chain.

00:46.360 --> 00:49.195
Yeah, I was thinking that
I would brief the committee

00:49.196 --> 00:51.097
on a fake op in Afghanistan.

00:51.098 --> 00:53.133
See if there was any Taliban response.

00:53.134 --> 00:54.434
A drip test.

00:54.435 --> 00:55.702
Right, drip test.

00:55.703 --> 00:58.470
I like it.

01:01.274 --> 01:02.876
But I don't like this.

01:02.877 --> 01:05.779
"White House. Now."

01:05.780 --> 01:07.212
Fresh nightmares.

01:07.601 --> 01:10.907
CDC just finished
tabulating overdose deaths

01:10.908 --> 01:11.974
from last year.

01:11.975 --> 01:13.075
How bad?

01:13.076 --> 01:14.510
Record-breaking.

01:14.511 --> 01:16.379
Well, I'm sorry to hear that,

01:16.380 --> 01:18.681
but shouldn't you have called
in a different cabinet member?

01:18.682 --> 01:19.782
The president already had

01:19.783 --> 01:22.185
the secretary of Health
and Human Services

01:22.186 --> 01:24.286
in the Oval this morning.

01:25.955 --> 01:27.990
Russell?

01:27.991 --> 01:30.393
Harrison's back in rehab.

01:30.394 --> 01:31.794
Oh, no.

01:31.795 --> 01:33.196
Ah, he's okay.

01:33.197 --> 01:35.759
Checked himself in last
week before he spiraled.

01:35.760 --> 01:37.560
Even managed to keep it out of the news,

01:37.561 --> 01:40.864
but when Conrad saw the CDC report...

01:40.865 --> 01:42.365
it became a busy morning.

01:42.366 --> 01:44.600
Do you know what he wants from me?

01:45.368 --> 01:47.502
Revenge.

01:49.539 --> 01:51.306
Good morning, Mr. President.

01:53.810 --> 01:55.578
Do you know how many American servicemen

01:55.579 --> 01:56.980
died in Vietnam, Bess?

01:56.981 --> 02:00.750
Uh, 58,000...

02:00.751 --> 02:02.685
58,220.

02:02.686 --> 02:04.521
In a war that lasted
more than ten years.

02:04.522 --> 02:06.356
Do you know how many Americans

02:06.357 --> 02:07.957
died of drug overdoses last year?

02:07.958 --> 02:09.859
- Well...
- 64,000.

02:09.860 --> 02:11.895
Mostly from opioids.

02:11.896 --> 02:14.697
It's the worst public
health crisis in a century.

02:14.698 --> 02:18.067
And it's happening on my watch.

02:18.068 --> 02:21.270
So I'm going to do something about it.

02:22.438 --> 02:25.341
Sergio Macias. You familiar?

02:25.342 --> 02:28.011
He's head of the Puebla
Cartel in Southern Mexico.

02:28.012 --> 02:30.013
He's in prison in Jalisco,

02:30.014 --> 02:32.816
but he's running things from his cell.

02:32.817 --> 02:34.384
That's why I want him
extradited to the U.S.

02:34.385 --> 02:35.718
and put into supermax.

02:35.719 --> 02:38.221
I'm not sure that's the right play, sir.

02:38.222 --> 02:39.656
Why the hell not?

02:39.657 --> 02:41.558
More than 90% of our
heroin comes from Mexico,

02:41.559 --> 02:43.560
and most of that from Macias.

02:43.561 --> 02:45.795
We extradite him, it'll
cripple his empire.

02:45.796 --> 02:48.565
And some new drug lord takes his place.

02:48.566 --> 02:51.167
If you want to focus on Mexico,

02:51.168 --> 02:53.570
we should focus on
government corruption.

02:53.571 --> 02:56.272
So you are content to let
Macias keep killing Americans?

02:56.273 --> 02:59.309
State's been holding talks

02:59.310 --> 03:04.480
with Mexico about new
anti-corruption measures,

03:04.481 --> 03:06.349
but it's delicate.

03:06.350 --> 03:08.852
If we push them to give up Macias,

03:08.853 --> 03:11.487
they won't want to cut any other deals.

03:11.488 --> 03:13.389
Fighting corruption is a noble goal,

03:13.390 --> 03:15.992
but I want Macias out of the equation.

03:15.993 --> 03:19.729
Opioid deaths are a systemic problem,

03:19.730 --> 03:21.631
a tragic one.

03:21.632 --> 03:24.234
So it's understandable
to want to find...

03:24.235 --> 03:27.136
We've known each other
a long time, Bess.

03:27.137 --> 03:28.605
You can talk to me straight.

03:28.606 --> 03:34.110
Russell told me about
Harrison, and I am, I'm so sorry

03:34.111 --> 03:36.878
for what you and Lydia
are going through.

03:38.681 --> 03:40.350
I'm worried that maybe

03:40.351 --> 03:41.951
it's clouding your judgment.

03:41.952 --> 03:43.519
Well, I understand your concern,

03:43.520 --> 03:46.189
but this isn't just about my son.

03:46.190 --> 03:47.724
I meet with families

03:47.725 --> 03:50.293
who've lost loved ones to
drugs almost every week.

03:50.294 --> 03:52.362
I can't keep giving them platitudes.

03:52.363 --> 03:54.197
I want decisive action today.

03:54.198 --> 03:56.399
Are we clear?

03:56.400 --> 03:59.235
Yes, Mr. President.

03:59.236 --> 04:00.637
- Morning.
- Good morning, ma'am.

04:00.638 --> 04:02.702
Uh, your call with the Mexican
secretary of foreign affairs

04:02.703 --> 04:05.408
- is in five minutes.
- Thanks. Are you okay?

04:05.409 --> 04:07.176
Yes. Why?

04:07.177 --> 04:09.379
Well, your blazer is unbuttoned.

04:09.380 --> 04:10.513
Oh, God.

04:10.514 --> 04:11.748
I'm so sorry.

04:11.749 --> 04:13.082
- No, that's not what I...
- It's, uh...

04:13.083 --> 04:14.284
...mean. It's, um, I'm just all...

04:14.285 --> 04:16.452
My parents are flying
into D.C. tomorrow.

04:16.452 --> 04:18.588
- Oh! Oh. Yeah.
- Yeah.

04:18.589 --> 04:20.589
That's... always a little challenging.

04:20.591 --> 04:22.547
- Yeah. Look, I-I love them
- I mean, I'm sure.

04:22.548 --> 04:23.593
More than anyone in the world.

04:23.594 --> 04:26.195
It's just... oh, sometimes
they make me so mad

04:26.196 --> 04:28.798
I want to rip the skin off my own face.

04:28.799 --> 04:31.467
Does that make sense?

04:31.468 --> 04:34.170
Yeah, I try not to
think about what my kids

04:34.171 --> 04:36.873
- think of me sometimes.
- Well, I doubt that you question

04:36.874 --> 04:39.409
their career and relationship
choices at every turn,

04:39.410 --> 04:41.911
- so I'm sure you're fine.
- How can they question your career choice?

04:41.912 --> 04:42.944
Well...

04:42.945 --> 04:45.548
You are literally
helping save the world.

04:45.549 --> 04:47.817
My parents are private sector people.

04:47.818 --> 04:50.954
They... To their mind, leaving finance

04:50.955 --> 04:53.957
to go work for the government
was like blasting a fire hose

04:53.958 --> 04:56.893
full of money off a
cliff into the abyss.

04:56.894 --> 04:59.529
Well, if they saw what you did,

04:59.530 --> 05:01.754
they'd be bragging to all your friends,

05:01.755 --> 05:02.465
- Well, I...
- all their friends.

05:02.466 --> 05:03.641
- Yeah.
- Oh, come on.

05:03.642 --> 05:04.934
You know what, bring 'em in.

05:04.935 --> 05:06.699
What? Oh, no. Thank you.

05:06.700 --> 05:07.879
- That's very kind of you. I...
- Yeah. No.

05:07.880 --> 05:09.405
We have been in this
relationship for years.

05:09.406 --> 05:13.141
It's time I met your parents, Blake.

05:15.511 --> 05:18.081
You are aware that Macias is in prison

05:18.082 --> 05:20.249
in Jalisco, Madam Secretary?

05:20.250 --> 05:21.517
Of course you are.

05:21.518 --> 05:23.519
You just don't trust our justice system.

05:23.520 --> 05:25.788
Secretary Gomez, I assure you

05:25.789 --> 05:29.459
this request is solely about
the U.S. justice system.

05:29.460 --> 05:32.829
Macias is wanted in seven states.

05:32.830 --> 05:35.498
He has indictments from nine

05:35.499 --> 05:36.466
federal courts.

05:36.467 --> 05:38.534
He is also a Mexican citizen,

05:38.535 --> 05:41.004
convicted by the Mexican judiciary.

05:41.005 --> 05:43.139
But why should you
respect our sovereignty?

05:43.140 --> 05:45.475
We have great respect for Mexico.

05:45.476 --> 05:49.445
In fact, I can guarantee
we will honor your laws

05:49.446 --> 05:51.781
and Macias won't face the death penalty.

05:51.782 --> 05:52.982
That is a start.

05:52.983 --> 05:55.118
But to even consider this deal,

05:55.119 --> 05:58.688
President Zaragoza wants
new trade provisions.

05:58.689 --> 06:01.924
Lift the restrictions on
cybersecurity software.

06:01.925 --> 06:04.660
Well, the Pentagon
doesn't give cyberweapons

06:04.661 --> 06:06.796
to any foreign country.

06:06.797 --> 06:08.664
I'm not talking about your military.

06:08.665 --> 06:10.166
Private companies.

06:10.167 --> 06:13.336
You have many burdensome
regulations around cyber trade

06:13.337 --> 06:14.337
with Mexico.

06:14.338 --> 06:15.805
Well, for good reason.

06:15.806 --> 06:17.840
Do you have any idea how hard it is

06:17.841 --> 06:20.443
to keep cyberweapons
away from bad actors?

06:20.444 --> 06:24.881
That is a rather galling lack
of faith for a close ally.

06:24.882 --> 06:27.784
It is a well-documented
fact that American guns

06:27.785 --> 06:29.952
have made their way to cartel hands.

06:29.953 --> 06:33.956
And a gun is a lot easier to
keep safe than a string of code.

06:33.957 --> 06:37.126
Once again, you know
what is best for Mexico.

06:37.127 --> 06:40.163
Can you just knock that off?

06:40.164 --> 06:42.632
I assure you that I am negotiating

06:42.633 --> 06:44.735
- in good faith.
- But we have nothing to negotiate.

06:44.736 --> 06:46.402
President Dalton wants Macias.

06:46.403 --> 06:48.438
Cyber is a priority
for President Zaragoza.

06:48.439 --> 06:50.740
You need to make it work. Or no deal.

06:50.741 --> 06:53.676
And tell your anti-corruption
unit to stand down.

06:53.677 --> 06:55.745
My government is no longer in the mood

06:55.746 --> 06:58.281
to be educated by your bureaucrats.

06:58.282 --> 06:59.649
Sec...

06:59.650 --> 07:01.950
...retary.

